import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['fertility'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across different countries?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['fertility', 'life_expect'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['fertility'], label='Fertility')
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'], label='Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['country_classification', 'fertility']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['country_classification'] == 'Developed']['fertility'], 
                data[data['country_classification'] == 'Developing']['fertility']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Developed', 'Developing'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Country Classification')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between country classification and fertility?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
